network_overview: The capture contains a single IMS/SIP registration exchange (REGISTER-100-200) over SCTP between UE 10.235.69.1 and P-CSCF 10.235.68.66; no voice call was attempted and no RTP/media streams are present. All SIP transactions completed successfully within 129 ms, so the apparent "FAILED" and "SETUP_TIMEOUT" labels in the JSON are false positives caused by the analytics tool mis-classifying a registration-only trace as a call attempt.

observations.finding: Only 5 packets exchanged: pure IMS signalling, zero user-plane traffic;完全符合开机后首次IMS注册场景
No INVITE, no BYE, no RTP; therefore no voice path established and no quality metrics to evaluate

root_causes.description: The VOICE & IMS ANALYSIS engine tagged the REGISTER transaction as a 'FAILED call' with 'SETUP_TIMEOUT', but no INVITE was ever sent; this is a registration-only flow that actually succeeded (200 OK received).
root_causes.impact: May trigger false alarms in SOC/NOC dashboards and waste troubleshooting effort.

recommendations.action: Filter analytics to classify only INVITE-initiated dialogs as 'calls'; treat stand-alone REGISTER as 'IMS-Reg' success/failure.
recommendations.rationale: Eliminates false positives and keeps KPIs aligned with 3GPP definition of call setup success.

recommendations.action: Enable periodic RTP-path probing (e.g., OPTIONS ping) to pre-verify firewall/NAT rules before first call.
recommendations.rationale: Ensures media ports are open so first call will not fail for user-plane reasons.

session_analysis.signaling_health: SIP/SCTP registration completed in 129 ms with no retransmissions or error codes; control plane healthy.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No GTP bearers observed; UE likely still in idle mode or default bearer only.
session_analysis.voice_quality: No RTP streams present; voice quality not applicable for this registration-only sample.
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Signaling plane ready; when UE later sends INVITE the same SCTP association will be reused, so bearer setup latency should be minimal.
